Good Afternoon Mustang Parents,
Is your child a transfer student to Palo Pinto ISD and needing transportation to and from school? Public Transit Services in Mineral Wells will provide that service for you. They must have 5 committed AM and PM student riders before they will come to Palo Pinto ISD. Please contact them for pricing and to be placed on their list. Don't wait too long, as school is right around the corner. You can reach them at (940) 328-1391, Hours are Monday through Friday 7:00 am-6:00 pm. Have a great week!!

Hello Mustang Parents,
The first day of school will be here before you know it. Please help us by completing your child’s online registration before the deadline on August 12, 2020. We realized yesterday a few were having issues getting the system to work. However, that glitch has now been fixed, so you are able to resume the registration process. Things to consider if a registration link is not provided on the Parent Portal page: 1. Use Google Chrome, 2. Be sure you use the same email address we have on file here in the office (if you're unsure, contact us), 3. You must verify your email and phone number. Also, please do not hesitate to contact us if you have any questions. (940) 659-2745 or ahinojos@palopintoisd.net

Please feel free to email me at ahinojos@palopintoisd.net over the weekend with any questions. Thank you and have a wonderful weekend!

Good Afternoon Mustang Parents,
This is an important reminder about completing our online survey.
Please take the time to visit our school website at www.palopintoisd.net
On the top right corner of PPISD website, you will see a tab for Covid-19, click the tab to open. There you will find 4 links, the first link is a Letter from Mr. Barker with FAQ's, the second link is our Public Health Plan, the third link is the Remote Learning Instruction Guide, and the fourth link is our Online Survey. Please review the links and take our survey before the deadline of August 3, 2020. This will help us determine numbers for on campus and remote instruction. I hope everyone has a wonderful day and we look forward to seeing your survey!!

Good afternoon Mustangs,

We would like to share information about the upcoming school year. Please understand that things related to COVID-19 change frequently- from the number of cases, to executive orders, and TEA recommendations. As circumstances demand, we will be updating all documents related to COVID-19 and remote learning.

All plans are now available under the COVID-19 tab of our school website (www.palopintoisd.net). Please continue to stay connected through our Palo Pinto website and Facebook.

Included in the COVID-19 tab is a survey for our Remote Learning option. Please take the time to fully read all plans before making the decision on Remote Learning.

If you have any questions feel free to email Natalie Rogers at nrogers@palopintoisd.net.

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
The Palo Pinto County office of Texas A&M AgriLife Extension Service will be offering a virtual program called Families Reading Every Day (FRED) this summer beginning June 1st. FRED is a 4-week FREE reading program where participants focus on reading together as a family. During the program, you enter daily reading logs of the number of books and time you read together as a family. FRED is a fun and effective way to strengthen family bonds and promote literacy development by encouraging families to focus on reading together. The FRED program is for adults with kids of all ages! All it takes is a commitment to spend time reading together.

The goal is 15 minutes a day for the first 2 weeks, and 30 minutes a day for the next 2 weeks but it could be more depending on the child's age and the adults involved.
Link to the FRED website https://fch.tamu.edu/fred/

shared_text:
Bat World Sanctuary
October 25, 2019 at 5:12 PM ·

We so love to hear things like this!! Mrs. Hamilton's Class in Palo Pinto, Texas has been watching our live bat cams as part of their lessons on respect and caring. Some of the students said they used to be so scared and hate bats. But, since watching our live stream cameras and learning more about bats, they are no longer scared and are eager to learn more. 😃👏

All of our future conservation efforts for bats will be found in children. Thank you, Mrs. Hamilton, for teaching the kiddos respect and caring for bats! This world needs more teachers like you. <3 🙌
text:
Bat World Sanctuary
October 25, 2019 at 5:12 PM ·

We so love to hear things like this!! Mrs. Hamilton's Class in Palo Pinto, Texas has been watching our live bat cams as part of their lessons on respect and caring. Some of the students said they used to be so scared and hate bats. But, since watching our live stream cameras and learning more about bats, they are no longer scared and are eager to learn more. 😃👏

All of our future conservation efforts for bats will be found in children. Thank you, Mrs. Hamilton, for teaching the kiddos respect and caring for bats! This world needs more teachers like you. <3 🙌

August 2, 2019 at 2:03 PM ·

Mustang Parents,

We hope you have had a wonderful summer so far! The PTO is going to be sending out newsletters each month to keep you all updated with what we have been up to.

We will be meeting every 3rd Wednesday at 3:45 PM in the computer lab. Your officers this year are, Donna Polston - President, Skye Dorr - Vice President, Katrina Porter - Secretary, Jennifer Nierman - Treasurer. We are all excited about this school year! We have some fun fundraisers planned! Stay tuned for details.

Meet the Teacher is August 15th at 3:30PM for Pre- K students and new students, and 4:30PM for returning students. We will be there with some treats and refreshments. Please speak with one of us if you have any questions about PTO or would like to volunteer.

The first day of school is August 19th. Please join us in the cafeteria for our Boohoo Yahoo breakfast after drop off, our treat!

We are looking forward to another wonderful school year!

Sincerely,
Palo Pinto PTO

March 20, 2019 at 10:12 AM ·

Mustang Merit Honorary Scholarship

Palo Pinto ISD is proud to offer a scholarship opportunity for current graduating seniors who plan to attend an institution of higher learning or enlist full-time in the armed forces immediately following graduation (summer or fall semester). There are criteria to apply. Applications are DUE no later than the 3rd Monday in April. Scholarship recipients will be notified by the 2nd Friday in May, contingent upon funds and the submission of quality applications. To determine eligibility and to apply, visit our district homepage at www.palopintoisd.net. Good luck to all of our Mustang alumni applicants!

🚨🚨 Attendance Drawing! 🚨🚨
Palo Pinto Elementary will be having an attendance drawing for a Nintendo Switch! We will start the first semester on Sept. 24th and end it on Dec. 17th, the second semester will start on Jan. 7th and end on May 17th. Students with 0 absences per semester will receive 3 tickets per semester, 1 absence per semester will receive 2 tickets per semester, and 2 absences per semester will receive 1 ticket per semester. We will have the official drawing on May 23rd. Please see parent flyer sent home or Palo Pinto ISD website for more details.
